item.description: 241. Different Ways to Add Parentheses iven a string of numbers and operators, return all possible results from computing all the different possible ways to group numbers and operators. The valid operators are +, - and *. Example 1: 1 2 3 4 5 Input: "2-1-1" Output: [0, 2] Explanation: ((2-1)-1) = 0 (2-(1-1)) = 2 Example 2: 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 8 Input: "2*3-4*5" Output: [-34,
